Xinhua Commentary: Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
People are the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talent?
The excellent group of returned migrant workers is an indispensable force.
By Haichun Shang, Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26th: Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands of yuan to return home and start a business.
After several years of hard work, he now runs a grape-growing family farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, and has become a well-known wealth leader. He has also been selected to join the "two committees" of the village.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support and benefit farmers, such as the country's poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home and start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population in the west of China and a large labor export province, implemented the "Excellent Migrant Workers Recruitment and Training Project" due to snobbery. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were produced from the excellent migrant workers, 61,000 village reserve forces were cultivated, and more than 20,000 party members were developed.
A well-off person is not a well-off person.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged workers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have established their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it has also led to the "hollowing out" of rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grassroots organizations, and the village party branch secretaries and party members have shown the characteristics of "one old and one low," that is, the age is aging, the education is low, the village party organization leaders are not strong, and the green and yellow problems are prominent.
If rural talents and other elements have been flowing in one direction to the city, and the countryside has been in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is an empty word.
Attracting back those migrant workers who are capable, conscious, and interested in serving their hometowns, guiding them to return to their hometowns and start businesses to become leaders in getting rich, selecting and training them to become party members and rural cadres, and enriching the ranks of grassroots cadres. This is the solution to the root cause of the shortage of rural party members and grassroots party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers should be brought back, and they should be allowed to stay and work well.
In recent years, Sichuan has begun to pay close attention to the construction of the migrant workers' party, and on the basis of strict selection criteria, has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted referral, service guarantee, training and promotion, and selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, have job security, and have hope in life, and really take root in the countryside, and have a sense of achievement in entrepreneurship.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty, and talent is the key factor to make the connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, build them into a working team and a new force that can be retained, can fight, and cannot be taken away, and provide strong organizational support and talent support for rural poverty alleviation and development and revitalization.
