Xinhua News Agency, Guangzhou, July 26 (Reporter Mao Xin) The reporter learned from the Guangdong Coast Guard Bureau that recently, the Bureau, together with the Guangzhou Customs and Public Security Department, defeated a large-scale smuggling gang of refined oil products, and preliminarily verified that the gang had smuggled about 120,000 tons of refined oil products since 2019, with a value of about 800 million yuan, and evaded taxes of about 240 million yuan.
The Guangdong Coast Guard Bureau and the Customs Anti-Smuggling Department have gradually figured out the division of labor and organizational structure of the gang.
