Jiangxi opens up a "green channel" for young people on the front line of flood control to enlist in the army - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Nanchang, July 26 (Guo Dongming, Xiong Liang) The Recruitment Office of the People's Government of Jiangxi Province recently made it clear that individuals or their children who have performed outstandingly in this flood rescue and disaster relief mission, meet the requirements for recruitment, and are qualified in both medical examination and political assessment, will be given priority.
"After the registration of the conscripted youth, we will give priority to the conscription after the verification of the community where the conscripted youth is located, the street armed forces department and the recruitment office of Poyang District."
Wang Hui, vice minister of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces of Poyang District, Jiujiang City, said that due to the impact of the floods, they began on the 25th and concentrated on organizing medical examinations for young conscripts for three days.
Zhou Jingfan, a 22-year-old college graduate from Poyang District, Jiujiang City, is a conscripted youth. His mother is a community worker, and his father is a veteran of a certain department of the Air Force. For the past ten days, Zhou Jingfan's parents have been on duty on the front line of flood control.
"These days, I see in the news that the people's soldiers are defending their hometown on the front line of the flood, and I want to be like them."
Zhou Jingfan said that he had a dream of joining the military since he was a child, and his determination to join the military camp was strengthened through this flood.
Jiujiang City also regards flood control and rescue as a "living textbook" for conscription propaganda. Taking the community as a unit, they call on conscripted young people to voluntarily participate in tasks such as patrolling dikes and being on duty, so as to understand the nature and purpose of the people's army on the spot and strengthen their confidence in joining the army and serving the country.
Luo Jiuyu, political commissar of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces of Poyang District, Jiujiang City, said that by giving priority to conscription, it is hoped to encourage more young conscripts and create a good social atmosphere in which it is glorious to participate in missions and join the army.
