The upgraded version of the Russian Ka-52M helicopter gunship will leave the factory for the first time at the end of the year - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Moscow, July 25th According to the plan of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the upgraded version of the Russian armed helicopter (hereinafter referred to as Wuzhi) Ka-52 - Ka-52M will be completed for the first time in December this year. The model will have a greater improvement in reconnaissance, communication and weapons performance.
According to a recent report by Russia's Izvestia newspaper, the Wuzhika-52M is called the "Super Alligator," and its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military-industrial units in April last year. At present, the first two of the upgraded version of the Wuzhika are undergoing transformation and refitting at the Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of the Russian "Progress" Aerospace Group Company. Its national-level testing and improvement will be completed by October 2022.
According to Russian experts familiar with the above-mentioned upgrade work, the "super alligator"'s "predecessor" - the WZ-52 - was officially put into service in November 2011. The model has exposed some weaknesses in use, and this transformation and upgrade is to "make up for the shortcomings."
The report said that compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will partly use new protective materials that do not add weight. Its pilot's cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to resist missile attacks, thereby increasing the probability of battlefield survival; it will be equipped with more powerful generators to power more complex on-board electronic equipment; the optoelectronic system will be upgraded to be able to detect and identify battlefield targets at greater distances; it will be equipped with a new light multi-purpose missile that mainly attacks armored combat vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications, with a range of 20 kilometers, which is about twice the range of similar missiles used by Russia's active armed forces; its defensive weapons and communication equipment will be maximally compatible with the Mi-28NM helicopter gunship that can attack air targets, making related maintenance easy and economical.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapons targeting systems and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is noteworthy that the Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with UAVs, so as to obtain real-time information transmitted by nearby UAVs in the air, such as displaying images taken by UAVs on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
According to the plan, the pilot of the Ka-52M can directly control the UAV with which it cooperates, thereby improving the pilot's grasp of the battlefield situation and the guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoruchko said in December last year that the Russian Ministry of Defense plans to buy more than 110 WZK-52Ms by 2027.
