"Stuffing Jiangnan" in Pursuit of the Poetic "Dream of the Yellow River"
(China's Poverty Reduction Story) "Stuck in the South of the Yangtze River" Pursuing the Poetic "Dream of the Yellow River"
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuquan Yellow River Wanli Sand, waves and winds from the end of the world. "
The Yellow River, which has aroused the pride of countless literati, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Today, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "stuffing Jiangnan," is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River dream."
River Qingshui's "Bibo Dream"
The Yellow River, which flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia, is the "mother river" of the nurturing side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, there is an imbalance between the development and utilization of rivers and lakes and the management and protection of rivers and lakes, and chaos such as excessive pollution, land reclamation around lakes, and encroachment on waters have become prominent, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of water ecological diversity and striving to restore the water quality of the Yellow River.
Water control must start at the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the "bidding + pollution control + strict management" approach, all the sewage in the industrial park was centralized, all the urban sewage treatment plants achieved the first-class A standard discharge, and the black and smelly water in the urban built-up area was basically eliminated, and the third batch of China's black and smelly water demonstration cities was successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake long system in 2017, and now has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake long system responsibility system in districts, cities, counties and villages, and river and lake long river patrol has become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, who lives in a village near the Yellow River, has witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: "The water used to have a bad smell, but after the renovation, the smell has disappeared."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is good, his life is more comfortable, and now he often goes to the Yellow River with his family to take a walk and feel the blue sky.
The "wetland dream" of Sha Xiangji
Flying birds, green trees, boardwalks, clear water... The beauty of Fan Zhongyan's "Sand Dragonfly Collection" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands, and swamp wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and the ecological balance of water, and has also become an internationally important bird migration channel.
Since 2009, the relevant departments of Ningxia have invested a total of about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, the wetland area of Yinchuan is 19,200 hectares, the wetland protection rate is 78.5%, there are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamp wetlands, and there are five national wetland parks, one national urban wetland park, six autonomous region-level wetland parks, and eight municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. "The widow is an endangered bird, there are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 inhabit the Yinchuan Wetland."
At the same time, Ningxia has legally delineated a red line of 500 meters between the wetland protection areas on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River, stipulating that except for public welfare projects, no unit or individual may carry out development, construction or business activities within the protected area.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the treatment of pollution sources, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology, and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of nine main drainage ditches in Ningxia has now reached 100% of Class IV standards. "Now the water is clear, the fish are swimming, and the flowers are blooming."
The "dream of drinking water" for universal people's livelihood
Yinchuan City in Ningxia once had an "embarrassing" title: the only city along the Yellow River that "guarded the Yellow River for lack of water to drink."
Since 2010, Yinchuan has been facing the problem of water shortage during the continuous summer peak, and the "pain of water shortage" in the past decade has become a painful summer experience for many high-rise residents. However, under the current situation where major water sources are at the limit of over-extraction and a large area of groundwater over-extraction funnel area has been formed under the urban area, water shortage has become a problem plaguing Yinchuan.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good way to solve the drinking water problems of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of the Yinchuan Municipal Water Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water needs of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia timely launched the Yinchuan Metropolitan Area Urban and Rural West Line Water Supply Project to replace the original groundwater source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project was officially opened to the three districts of Yinchuan City, and in 2020, residents of Yining Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River water."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will consider the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. "In the next step, we will integrate the scattered rural water supply points and connect them all to the western water supply project. It is expected that the urban and rural integrated water supply in Yinchuan will be basically realized by the end of this year."
