Lewis family: John Lewis was a 'fighter for the weakest'
US Congressman and civil rights champion John Lewis was remembered at a memorial service for him on Saturday (July 25) as a fighter who "fought for the weakest."
Public memorial services for Lewis have been held in Alabama since Saturday.
There were two memorial services on the first day.
At a public memorial service at Troy University in Alabama on Saturday, Lewis' five siblings and a great-nephew spoke of him as a loving, fearless, family-oriented man.
"He dedicated his life to helping others," Lewis' youngest brother, Henry "Grant" Lewis, said at the meeting.
Samuel Lewis said his mother had warned John to "stay out of trouble, stay out of trouble."
He added that John did not heed his mother's warning, saying: "We all know that John was always getting into trouble, always getting into trouble, but it was for standing up for what was right, a good trouble."
Lewis's siblings reminded people at the memorial service that John's most famous argument was to make "good trouble," that is, to stir up trouble as long as it was for justice.
John had applied to Troy University in his native city of Troy, Alabama, but the then all-white school rejected his application.
John Lewis, who as a child preached the gospel to chickens on his family farm, eventually earned a degree in religion and philosophy from Fisk University.
Years later, Troy University awarded Lewis an honorary doctorate.
Doug Jones, a U.S. senator from Alabama, said the current protesters "are protesting peacefully and nonviolently," just as Lewis did during the civil rights movement.
Jones said: "Even if President Trump knocked over a boatload of people and called all the protesters thugs, he was wrong.
The protesters are patriots who want America to move toward a more equal country."
A six-day series of events honoring Lewis will culminate in his funeral in Georgia this week.
Lewis' coffin lay in state at a public memorial at Troy University on Saturday, where people came to pay their respects to the civil rights pioneer.
Later Saturday, a private ceremony paid tribute to him at a chapel in Selma, Alabama, followed by a public memorial.
On Sunday, Lewis' body will cross the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma.
It was in front of this bridge in 1965 that he and demonstrators demanding the right to vote for blacks were beaten by Alabama police, who also fired tear gas at demonstrators.
Lewis was nearly killed.
The day would become known as "Bloody Sunday."
Lewis' body will be transported to Alabama's capital, Montgomery.
Mayor Steven Reed encouraged people to line the sidewalks and walk with Lewis on his final journey.
At the same time, officials asked the public to wear masks and maintain social distance when participating in activities.
Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey ordered flags to be flown at half-staff Saturday and Sunday in honor of Lewis.
Lewis' body will lie in state briefly at the Alabama State Capitol in Montgomery, the Georgia State Capitol in Atlanta and the U.S. Capitol in Washington during the nearly week-long commemoration.
U.S. House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell announced last week that people can pay their respects to Lewis at the U.S. Capitol this Monday and Tuesday.
Due to the coronavirus pandemic, the public event to honor Lewis will be held outdoors.
Shenzhen launches public consultation on health regulations - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporters Mao Sijun and Bai Yu) Encourage residents to do physical examinations diligently to detect problems early; prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establish a health review system for online games; employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health managers... Recently, the "Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Draft for Comment) " was officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law."
In order to encourage residents to do physical examinations diligently and detect problems early, the above-mentioned draft for comments proposes that the health and health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health examination items according to different age, occupation and other factors.
The cost of health check-ups that fall within the scope of the basic catalogue of health check-up items shall be paid by the social medical insurance co-ordinating fund according to the standard of once a year per person.
The draft for comments makes it clear that employers should rationally allocate human resources, arrange employees' working hours, implement a rotation system for employees with heavy mental and physical workloads, avoid excessive loss of human functions or physical and mental health damage to employees' health, and strictly implement the paid leave system for employees.
In addition, employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health managers, and organize regular health checkups for employees.
In terms of the physical and mental health of minors, the draft for comments proposes to prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors, while restricting the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages.
In addition to "no alcohol," minors should also "exercise more."
According to the requirements of the draft, schools should arrange more than one hour of physical activity for students every day.
For online games, the public security, culture, radio, television, tourism and sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet access service business sites, establish a health review system for online games, and create a good communication space and communication culture for promoting the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and medical and health institutions should be fined 20,000 yuan for disclosing patient privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft for comments also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population before formulating plans, normative documents, and approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects involving urban space planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization and ecological environmental protection, and biomedical industry development.
If it has not been evaluated or if it will have a more serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents, it shall not be enacted or approved for implementation.
