More than 6,000 pentagonal heliostats, each 48 square meters, are arranged neatly in a circle, like a silver "sunflower field," which rotates with the sun and reflects sunlight to the central 200-meter-high heat-absorbing tower to generate electricity.
The reporter saw this scene on the 25th at the Hami molten salt tower solar-thermal power plant of the CLP project in Manmaohu Town, Yiwu County, Hami City, Xinjiang.
"The so-called molten salt tower solar thermal power generation is to reflect the sunlight through the mirror to the heat-absorbing tower to form thermal energy, and then convert the thermal energy into electricity through traditional power generation technology."
