"Compared with traditional solar power technology, its biggest advantage is that it can store the accumulated heat energy and generate electricity at night."
Zhang Yong said that the 13-hour heat storage system configured in the project can enable the generator set to maintain continuous and stable operation without being affected by changes in light; it can also quickly participate in peak shaving of the grid according to the peak and valley demand of the grid load.
When the project is fully completed, it will achieve an annual power generation capacity of 198 million kWh, save more than 60,000 tons of standard coal per year, reduce emissions of more than 60 tons of sulfur dioxide, more than 60 tons of nitrogen oxides, about 20 tons of soot, and more than 150,000 tons of carbon dioxide, and provide a steady stream of clean energy for the local area.
