France to increase military investment in space - Xinhua
French Defense Minister Florence Parly said on the 24th that France will add hundreds of millions of euros to the space defense budget and develop space military forces to prevent "unfriendly actions" that other countries may carry out in outer space.
Parly told La Provence on the same day that between 2019 and 2025, France's budget for military space projects will increase from the previously proposed 3.6 billion euros ($4.2 billion) to 4.3 billion euros ($5 billion).
According to the French Military Planning Act for 2019-2025 approved by the French Parliament in 2018, France is expected to update the existing observation satellites and communication satellites, launch three electromagnetic interception satellites, and improve the modernization of space surveillance radars.
French President Emmanuel Macron announced last July that a military space command and an "aviation and space force" would be created within the French Air Force.
Parly said she would formally announce the creation of the space force later during a visit to a military school in Salon-de-Provence.
Parly said the Space Force, which is part of the Air Force, will have 500 people by 2025.
"Gone is the idea that space serves the common good of science," she said. "Today, space is a place where nations compete for global supremacy."
Parly reiterated Macron's previous statement, saying that France has no intention of provoking an arms race.
"We are by no means in an arms race. But it is my responsibility to be thoroughly aware of the threats we may face."
Parly recalled the 2017 surveillance of a military satellite shared by France and Italy.
She said that it was a Russian satellite that was "peeping."
Russia denies the claim.
Parly said France would "soon" have small patrol satellites capable of detecting and targeting "those behind unfriendly moves."
French media believe that the reason why France is seeking to establish a space force is that US President Donald Trump asked the US Department of Defense to draft a bill to establish a space force in February last year.
Trump signed the National Defense Authorization Act last December, approving the establishment of the Space Force, the sixth branch of the US military.
Some experts fear that these US initiatives have accelerated the pace of US space militarization and may trigger a new round of space arms race.
