The report said that the shared accommodation market began to pick up in March
According to the "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market fell by 72.1% year-on-year in the first five months of 2020 due to the impact of the epidemic.
However, the shared accommodation market has started to pick up since March, and the market turnover, order volume and reception number have gradually recovered.
The "Report" shows that the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market has fallen sharply. On the one hand, due to the sharp decline in the demand for travel accommodation under the prevention and control of the epidemic, the order volume has decreased sharply, and the total order volume in the first five months has dropped by 65% year-on-year, and the number of visitors has dropped by 63% year-on-year. On the other hand, the weak demand has also led to a significant decline in the price of overnight stays, and the average nightly price in the first five months has dropped by 16% year-on-year.
However, in March, April, and May, the market turnover increased by 78%, 199%, and 35% respectively; the number of orders increased by 141%, 152%, and 50% respectively; and the number of visitors increased by 81%, 112%, and 28% respectively.
The report pointed out that the development of the shared accommodation industry is promising in the long run, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, told the "Workers' Daily" reporter that the development of shared accommodation needs stronger policy support. On the one hand, it is necessary to implement the policies that have been introduced in the early stage, further strengthen policy promotion, and focus on creating a better business environment. On the other hand, it is also necessary to further increase policy guidance and support from various aspects such as stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourist accommodation services, innovating service methods, and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform companies.
