Xiamen, July 26 (Xinhua) -- China's famous vascular surgery center, the Vascular Surgery Department of Shanghai Changhai Hospital of the Naval Medical University, signed a contract with the Vascular Surgery Department of Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University on the 25th to jointly set up a collaboration center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the field of vascular surgery, especially in the field of aortic emergency.
Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, said that after the vascular surgery of the two hospitals officially formed a collaborative unit, it will carry out remote consultation, formulate treatment plans with Changhai Hospital in real-time online consultation, select and send talents for further training, and jointly carry out surgical technology exchanges and teaching room inspections every week. For complex cases, Changhai experts can be invited to the hospital to perform surgery according to the needs of patients, so that patients in southwest China can enjoy the top medical resources in the country without leaving the province.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out innovative scientific research on surgery, popularization of aortic diseases and early screening.
A special seminar on the aorta was held in Xiamen on the same day, sponsored by the Beijing Health Promotion Association and hosted by the Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University.
At the same time, the above-mentioned two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Shanghai held a signing ceremony for the Vascular Surgery Collaborative Center and announced the formation of a collaborative unit to jointly improve the treatment level of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest China.
Shanghai Changhai Hospital Vascular Surgery is the only vascular surgery institute in the army and the only clinical medical center for vascular system diseases in Shanghai. It is also the first national key discipline of vascular surgery. It led the establishment of the Professional Committee of Endovascular Angiology of the Chinese Medical Association and is a top team with deep accumulation in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of vascular surgery at the Zhongshan Hospital of Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
The vascular surgery department of Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, is the first independent vascular surgery department in Fujian Province, and has long been committed to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases. In 2018, it was approved to build a provincial key clinical specialty.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissecting aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he has extensive experience in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysms.
"The vascular surgery of Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University is very outstanding in the region in terms of the history of development, the breadth, difficulty and complexity of surgery, so this time we set up a collaboration center. In addition to the aorta, we can also carry out in-depth cooperation in medicine, teaching and research in the diagnosis and treatment of diseases such as lower limb arteries and carotid arteries."
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital, affiliated with Xiamen University, and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract in 2018 to establish the "Li Zhaoshen Famous Medical Studio" in Gastroenterology.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of the hospital's vascular surgery department, said in an interview with China News Network that the hospital's vascular surgery department has also had a long history of exchanges with Changhai Hospital. The two hospitals have officially formed a collaborative unit, bringing the cooperation and exchange between the two sides to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to Xiamen to carry out surgical technology exchanges, teaching room inspections, and discussion of difficult cases. At the same time, it will further carry out remote consultation, and currently plans to conduct remote consultation once a week. In addition, the department will also select personnel for further training and exchange, and strengthen the training and development of disciplinary personnel.
The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the number one cause of death in China, and the aorta plays an important role as the main artery of various organs in the human body, flowing from the heart to the whole body.
The occurrence of aortic disease is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty of treatment. The thickest section of the aorta has a diameter of 4 cm. Once a hemangioma forms, a rupture occurs, or a rupture of the blood vessel lining produces a dissection, which will cause major bleeding and is very dangerous.
In recent years, as people's lifestyles have changed and the pace of life has accelerated, China has become the world's largest country with high blood pressure, and aortic diseases have also increased. Today, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
Doctors can achieve good treatment results by puncturing the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta to properly "divert" the blood flow, thereby avoiding the impact on the aneurysm or ruptured dissection. Some operations even require only local anesthesia.
This academic symposium invited more than ten domestic experts to discuss new advances in the treatment of aortic diseases, and carried out cutting-edge technical training and discussion of difficult cases in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
