The longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir area
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel.
China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Company Profile
China News Service, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Wei) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers, was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel within the Three Gorges Reservoir area, but also the longest single-hole double-line high-speed rail tunnel with a design speed of 350 km/h in the projects currently under construction in China.
Located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing, the Zhengwan high-speed railway connects with the Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railways in the north of Zhengzhou, and reaches Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of the river channel and the Hunan channel in China's "eight vertical and eight horizontal" high-speed railway network.
The Zhengwan High-speed Railway's Little Three Gorges Tunnel was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows the scene of the breakthrough.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, and Xiangyang City, Hubei Province, to Wanzhou District, Chongqing City. The new line has a total length of about 818 kilometers and a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, with about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has started operation on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which was completed on the 26th, is a control project for the entire line of the Zhengwan High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017, and the entire line was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, head of high-speed rail tunnel design at China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey designer, the terrain and geological conditions of the location of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex, facing risks such as karst, muddy water, and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Class I high-risk tunnel, and tunnel design and construction are extremely difficult.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey, geophysical prospecting and advanced drilling methods to advance geological forecasting, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 types of caves. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built to cross a large cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement," said Wang Guojun.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction party, during the construction of the tunnel, a combination of dredging and plugging was adopted. Through the construction of horizontal tunnel leveling, grouting and water plugging, strengthening the structural support of the tunnel and the construction of a sewage treatment station, it not only ensured the orderly progress of the project, but also avoided the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcame the construction problems of bad geology such as the large deformation of soft rock for up to 7 kilometers, and the maximum daily water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters of muddy water.
After the Zhengwan high-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport main channel in southwest China to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast railway channel in southwest China, improve the layout of the regional road network, accelerate the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the line, promote coordinated regional development, and promote the implementation of the western development strategy.
