China News Network, Qinghai, Hainan, July 26th, title: Qinghai Lake "Flower Sea Live Room": "Sweet" with goods to help farmers increase income
Author Hu Guilong Pan Yujie
"In midsummer, Qinghai Lake is full of golden flowers and flying bees. Here, the altitude is higher, the temperature difference between day and night is large, the air pollution is less, and the strong light gives birth to the most tenacious and generous bee colony, creating the characteristics of Qinghai royal jelly with high activity, high protein, rich nutritional value, low sugar and low fat."
On the 26th, Zhang Jianxun, deputy director of the Industry and Information Administration of Hainan Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, Qinghai Province, said.
On the same day, the live delivery of bee products was held on the shore of Qinghai Lake. The China Bee Products Association, representatives of entrepreneurs, bee farmers and other parties gathered together to promote Qinghai's characteristic bee products. A total of nearly 10,000 bottles of Qinghai Plateau royal jelly were sold online and offline, with a total delivery of nearly 3.8 million yuan.
The picture shows beekeepers displaying bee products on the spot.
It is reported that with the help of Beijing Houdeli Bee Industry Chain Store Network, Kuaishou, Taobao and other well-known domestic bee product retail enterprises, live broadcast and e-commerce platforms, the live broadcast and delivery activities have promoted the exchange and cooperation of "enterprises + beekeepers + growers" and continued to issue "Qinghai Plateau Spring Pulp Consumption Vouchers" to consumers through online and offline channels. It is expected that the total annual profit of enterprises will be nearly 5.28 million yuan.
In this regard, Zou Na, president of Beijing Houdeli Bee Industry Co., Ltd., believes that "it is worth it": "This move can expand the popularity of Qinghai bee products, attract more consumers to understand and like pure natural bee products without additives, and drive bee farmers to increase their income."
At present, the company has signed a production cooperation strategic agreement with Qinghai Cloud Bee Industry Co., Ltd. and Qinghai Huabao Bee Industry Joint Stock Cooperation Company, hoping to jointly promote the rapid development of the local bee industry in Qinghai.
The picture shows a sea of rapeseed flowers on the shore of Qinghai Lake.
This spring, due to the need to set up road access checkpoints for epidemic prevention and control, beekeepers were blocked from "chasing flowers and honey." Many bees died due to missed flowering and lack of food, and the income of beekeepers was seriously affected.
"Throughout the year, beekeepers travel long distances to follow the flowering period, moving from Yunnan and Sichuan all the way north to the northwest region, where they sleep rough and have no fixed abode, which is very hard.
As a business, we have a responsibility to help them."
Tina said.
"Small bees are 'environmental scouts', and bees cannot survive in heavily polluted areas," said Zhao Xiaochuan, executive vice president of the China Bee Products Association. Bee pollination is an important link in the ecological chain and plays an irreplaceable role in protecting plant diversity and improving the ecological environment.
At the same time, bee pollination can increase the yield and quality of crops, especially in areas with wide varieties and poor management conditions.
According to research data, pollination can increase the yield of rape by about 15%-30%.
The picture shows Zhao Xiaochuan (right), executive vice president of the China Bee Products Association, promoting Qinghai bee products.
"The economic, ecological and social benefits created by bee pollination are far greater than the value of bee products themselves, and the bee industry has great potential in human health, crop production, vegetation reproduction and ecological protection, which has been poorly understood."
Zhao Xiaochuan said.
Nowadays, the number of beekeepers is getting smaller and smaller. In addition to beekeepers who are on the move all year round, there are still many poor households with limited mobility who choose to invest in cooperatives with beehives.
"The state has financial support, we contact technical personnel to help guide, bee farmers lack understanding and judgment of the market environment, to open the market also need the help and coordination of the government, enterprises and industry associations."
Zhao Xiaochuan said.
"I hope that everyone will pay more attention to and help the beekeeping community in the future," said Gong Na. "Our bee products are also screened and controlled in strict accordance with national standards to ensure quality and protect consumer rights while helping beekeepers."
