According to an article published in The Lancet on the 25th, China, as a country with a population of 1.4 billion and a size similar to that of Europe or the United States, has effectively controlled the new coronavirus epidemic at this stage, and there has been no further widespread transmission, which has largely controlled the domestic epidemic.
The article said that in the past decade or so, China has invested heavily in domestic research and public health construction, which has made China much more prepared for the new coronavirus than it was for severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS).
