The soldiers had to use their hands and feet to climb the steep slope of the rock pile.
It was late July, when low-altitude areas are lush with flowers, and only in the ravine behind the barracks was there a relatively dense green in Ba Rong Cho Kang.
Gao Peng, a soldier who has been stationed at the post for six years, pointed to the ravine and said that this is their back garden, and only in July and August each year can they see the grass grow slowly, and soon after, it all turns yellow and is covered by snow.
