In the first half of the year, the crime of telecommunication network fraud increased by 70%.
China News Service, July 26th According to the Supreme People's Procuratorate website, in the first half of this year, the national procuratorial organs prosecuted a total of 58,101 people for fraud crimes, an increase of 35% year on year.
In particular, among the crimes that obstruct epidemic prevention and control, fraud crimes are frequent, and the number of fraud crimes prosecuted by procuratorial organs accounts for 43.4% of the total number of crimes that obstruct epidemic prevention and control.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance, and of the ten batches of typical cases related to epidemic prevention and control that have been released so far, a total of nine involve fraud.
Judging from the handling of cases by procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are many names involved in fraud crimes, ranging from national macro policies to ordinary people's food, clothing and housing, including epidemic-related fraud, "medical care" fraud, "health care products" fraud, "enrollment intermediary" fraud, "routine loan" fraud, defrauding state subsidies fraud, national assets unfreezing fraud, etc. The scope involves education, medical care, employment, pension, social security, land acquisition and demolition, precision poverty alleviation, financial credit and other fields, which not only cause economic losses to victims, but also seriously affect economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunications network frauds break through the restrictions of national borders, regions and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholder, cross-border, remote and electronic payment, with many unspecified victim groups and great harm.
For example, some set up special companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or positions, use legitimate online platforms to promote and recruit, train and assess recruiters, and adopt enterprise operation mode management, wearing a "legal cloak," which is more confusing.
It is the bounden duty of the procuratorate to punish and prevent crimes in accordance with the law, and to issue timely warnings to the public and relevant departments.
In the judicial handling of cases, the procuratorial organs conscientiously perform their duties, not only insisting on maintaining a high-pressure attitude towards fraud crimes, but also refining various law enforcement measures in a targeted manner, and promoting social governance by formulating and issuing procuratorial recommendations.
The procuratorate strictly controls the facts, evidence, procedures and application of the law in approving arrests and prosecuting fraud cases, taking the facts as the basis and the law as the criterion.
Especially for the crime of telecommunication network fraud, we pay attention to the central role of electronic data in the determination of facts, and strive to build a chain of evidence between electronic data, verbal evidence, and documentary evidence.
For example, in response to an epidemic-related fraud case handled by the Zhangzhou District Procuratorate in Ningbo, Zhejiang Province, the procuratorate intervened in advance at the first time, and it took only 5 days from the occurrence of the case to the conclusion, reflecting the attitude and determination to handle it quickly and strictly and maintain the overall stability of the society.
In the review of arrests and review of prosecutions, attention was paid to the prosecution of cases of omitted offenders, correcting the omission of public security organs to arrest 733 people, and correcting the omission of public security organs to review and prosecute 1,113 co-offenders.
In the first half of the year, the national procuratorate issued 298 procuratorial recommendations on fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promote in-depth governance.
For example, in response to the loopholes in the supervision of telecommunications networks found in the case of communication enterprises, banks, intermediary organizations, etc., the Guangzhou Municipal Procuratorate and the Dongguan Municipal Procuratorate of Guangdong Province promptly put forward procuratorial recommendations, urging relevant units to strengthen supervision and improve mechanisms to promote the construction of a long-term system.
The fourth is to do a good job of recovering losses.
Local procuratorial organs have seized the important links of intervening in investigation, guiding evidence collection, reviewing and prosecuting, urging investigative organs to actively recover stolen money, cooperating with relevant departments to do a good job in recovering losses, and striving to minimize the economic losses caused by fraud crimes to the people.
For example, in the case of Lin Moumou's road loan case handled by the Beijing Municipal Procuratorate, which involved 22 sets of real estate waiting to be seized, in the case that the real estate may be disposed of by other cases first, the "Suspended Execution Letter" was first issued and delivered to the relevant court in a timely manner. It is recommended that the court suspend the execution of the real estate involved in the case before the seizure, and dispose of it uniformly after the criminal facts are ascertained, and make the greatest effort to recover the real estate involved and recover the losses of the victims.
The prosecutor reminded everyone to be very vigilant against fraud and crime, not to expect "pie in the sky," and not to believe that it is cheap, and to guard their "money bags."
Jina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province: Shortening the Apple Tree and Widening the Road Out of Poverty
2020-07-26 11:42:58 Source: China Economic Net Author: Zhu Yanjing Editor: Zhu Yanjing
In the scorching heat, a reporter from the Economic Daily - China Economic Net walked into Zhonghai Village in Jina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province.
Under the scorching sun, villager Li Yuanzhong mowed grass at the base. Although his face was red from the sun, he hummed a few ditties from time to time.
Weining County, where Jina Town is located, has a certain reputation in the surrounding area due to its low latitude, high altitude, sufficient light, large temperature difference between day and night, high sugar content and good taste of apples, but also because of its small size and many spots, it has not been able to sell a good price and has not formed an industrial scale.
Jina Town was once a poverty-stricken township that "packed grain and potatoes for the spring and autumn," and the local poverty rate was as high as 25.8% 10 years ago.
In the crucial period when the fight against poverty has entered a decisive battle, it is urgent to change traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure, and increase farmers' income.
After many visits, Chen Chao, the party secretary of Jina Town, and a group of people in the town believe that industrial development can no longer follow the old path.
To this end, the town of Jina introduced leading enterprises to grow apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Beyond Agriculture Co., Ltd., came to Jina Town from Shaanxi in 2015 to investigate, and saw the local planting conditions at a glance, and began to plant apple trees there in 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees, and Li Yuanzhong and his wife muttered in their hearts: "After growing apples for so many years, I have not seen anyone in the village grow apples and make a fortune."
"The apples planted are dwarf apples, which will not make the apple tree grow too tall."
What Li Yuanzhong did not expect was that the apple planting used a new method. Irrigation pipes were laid under each apple tree, water and fertilizer were poured to the roots, and when the fruit was harvested in autumn, the tractor drove directly into the orchard and could pick the fruit while standing.
At present, the apple base has gradually entered a period of abundant production, and the market is just as Hou Jianwen expected. Apple is not worried about selling, and is deeply loved by consumers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and other cities.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life. Although he is still farming, he has a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family has more than 9 acres of land transferred to the Apple base. Every year, in addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee, there are profit dividends after hanging fruit. The couple usually works in the base, "one person can get 80 yuan per day, and there is work all year round."
Li Yuanzhong told reporters that last year's profit dividend was more than 2,800 yuan, and with the land transfer fee and the couple's labor income, the family's income was more than 80,000 yuan.
"At present, it has achieved initial results, and the annual output value of 1 mu of apples exceeds 15,000 yuan, which is about 10 times that of corn."
Chen Chao told reporters that at present, the whole town of Jina has planted 20,000 mu of apples, and there are 6,000 mu in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 households and 17,200 people, including 656 households and 2,952 people in poor households with filing cards, and more than 6 million yuan in wages a year.
Li Yuanzhong, whose pockets are increasingly bulging, has also begun to realize his "wish."
This year's Lunar New Year, Li Yuanzhong bought an off-road vehicle, such as driving a car to and from work today, "there are still more than ten acres of land at home, and when the next step is to expand the scale of the Apple base, all of them will be transferred to them, and the income will be more."
