There are three types of professional assignment rules
Experts remind that before filling in the volunteer application, you must read the "Admissions Regulations" of your favorite school in detail and understand the admission rules of the university, including the transfer ratio and the professional allocation rules.
The professional assignment rule means that after the transfer of colleges and universities, there are mainly three ways for professional admission: professional priority, score priority, and professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be made clear in the Admissions Regulations.
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is that the total score is preferred, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, the candidates within the admission range will be lined up according to the total score, and when the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score line, it will be seen whether the second professional volunteer admission score line has been reached, and so on until the last professional volunteer is admitted, and there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" is that colleges and universities, when arranging candidates' majors, determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates in different majors according to one or several score values published in the admissions regulations. This score value is "professional grade difference."
That is, the difference between the scores of the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer, and the difference between the scores of each professional volunteer, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Assuming that the student Xiaoming applied for college A and scored 560 points, his professional volunteers were: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce, and the professional admission of college A implemented the method of professional grade difference, the grade difference was divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, and 0 points.
In the professional assignment, if Xiaoming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the professional has a planned balance, then Xiaoming is admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and the score of 558 points will be sorted with the candidates of the first professional volunteer to apply for "international trade" to determine whether they meet the professional admission conditions; if they still cannot meet, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (that is, 557 points) for the admission of the third professional volunteer "automation"; if they still cannot meet, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (that is, 556 points) for the admission of the fourth professional, and the subsequent professional will not be deducted if they still cannot meet their professional volunteer, and so on.
Different universities set different grades for different majors
With the popularity of parallel volunteering, many universities have now abolished the professional grade difference, but this year there are still some universities that have retained this method. Judging from the "Admissions Regulations" published by each school, more than 20 universities have set up professional grade differences this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, and China Civil Aviation Flight Academy.
Among these universities, each university sets a different professional level.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University, and the candidates whose files have been submitted to the school are admitted in order of score after decreasing by 1 point according to the order in which the candidates fill in the major volunteer.
And some universities have set different professional levels between different majors.
For example, at Jimei University, the total score of professional volunteer grade difference is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points, there is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteering, and the difference between other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling out the volunteer application, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is a professional grade difference and what the form of the grade difference is. While fully considering the score, it is also necessary to rationally analyze the schools and majors to be selected. If the institution clearly adopts the score difference method for admission in the enrollment charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors when choosing a major to improve the admission rate.
Lin Wei, Upstream News Reporter, Chongqing Morning Post
The first Atlantic hurricane of the year makes landfall in hard-hit Texas
The US National Hurricane Center announced in the morning that Hurricane Hanna reached 145 kilometers per hour and is expected to cause heavy rainfall in southern Texas and northeastern Mexico until next Monday, and the rainfall will cause rapid flooding.
At present, with the gradual advance to the land, the custom has weakened, and although there are power outages in some areas, there are no casualty statistics reported for the time being.
Some local officials in Texas are preparing for a strong possibility of tornadoes along the coast.
President Trump said via Twitter that the office is closely monitoring the dynamics of Hurricane Hanna and Hurricane Douglas in Hawaii, and called on the public to listen to the local government's emergency management information to protect families and property.
At the same time, the new coronavirus outbreak in Texas is also deteriorating sharply, and the number of infections is soaring, with more than 390,000 confirmed infections and more than 5,000 deaths.
When the hurricane hits, the government will face the dual challenge of sheltering the homeless while preventing the epidemic from worsening again.
For the first time, a special committee was set up to collectively sign a "long-term contract" for the third CIIE exhibitor alliance to build a "CIIE bond" - Xinhua
The scene of the first meeting of the 3rd CIIE Exhibitor Alliance in Shanghai on July 26.
Xinhua News Agency, Shanghai, July 26 (Reporter Zhou Rui) On the 26th, the Exhibitor Alliance of the Third Import Expo established a professional committee for the first time here. The first special committees established included the Public Health and Epidemic Prevention Special Committee and the Dairy Special Committee. 35 member companies also signed a three-year long-term exhibition cooperation memorandum, and the bond of the Expo Exhibitor Alliance continued to increase.
At the first meeting of the Exhibitor Alliance of the third CIIE held here on the 26th, a group of member companies of the exhibition alliance, including Hyundai of Korea, Dow Chemical of the United States, Shiseido of Japan, New Zealand New Zealand, Siemens of Germany, Michelin of France and AstraZeneca of the United Kingdom, signed a three-year long-term exhibition cooperation memorandum. The revised and improved exhibition alliance charter was also announced for the first time.
The scene of the founding ceremony of the Dairy Professional Committee in Shanghai on July 26.
According to the latest charter, the exhibition alliance will introduce a rotation mechanism for leading units and strengthen the function of the special committee.
The special committee will make recommendations for the analysis of industry development trends and promote the sustainable development of the industry.
At the same time, the integration of the industry's entire industrial chain resources, with large and small, will drive affiliated enterprises to participate in the exhibition, and build the Expo into a highland for industry enterprises to gather.
The establishment of a special committee on public health and epidemic prevention for the first time is particularly important for the current fight against the new coronavirus.
As the vice chairman of the public health and epidemic prevention special committee of the third CIIE, Qiu Jianping, general manager of Abbott's rapid diagnosis business in Greater China, said that in the next step, Abbott will work with more industry partners to explore new solutions and cooperation models to help China and the world fight the new coronavirus epidemic.
The scene of the founding ceremony of the Professional Committee for Public Health and Epidemic Prevention in Shanghai on July 26.
It is reported that the third CIIE has set up a public health epidemic prevention zone for the first time. So far, nearly 50 global companies have registered to participate in the exhibition, with an exhibition area of more than 10,000 square meters.
During the first CIIE in 2018, the CIIE Exhibitor Alliance was established on the initiative of exhibitors. It aims to become a platform for high-quality exhibitors to exchange and cooperate, a platform for connecting exhibitors to share information and resources, and a think tank platform for promoting economic, trade and business exchanges and development between China and countries (regions) around the world.
Up to now, 142 companies have joined the exhibitor alliance, covering 23 countries and regions around the world.
Three-year-old girl dies of new coronavirus infection in Belgium - Xinhua
Belgian health authorities said on the 24th that a 3-year-old girl died of new coronavirus infection, the youngest new coronavirus death in the country.
Budwin Katri, a spokesman for the Belgian health department, said that the girl had other serious diseases before she was infected with the new coronavirus; in addition to the girl, an 18-year-old recently died of the new coronavirus infection.
Katri said that last week, 85% of the newly diagnosed people in Belgium were under the age of 60.
He cautioned healthy, younger people not to take it lightly.
"Although it is rare for young people to die from the new coronavirus infection, no one is now immune."
Last week, Belgium's new confirmed cases of new coronavirus increased by 89% from the previous week, and an average of 2.9 people died of new coronavirus infection every day, up from an average of 1.7 people per day in the previous week.
During the peak of the European epidemic, the proportion of new coronavirus infections in the Belgian population was among the highest in Europe.
Belgium has a population of more than 11 million.
The latest data shows that a total of 64,847 people in Belgium have been infected with the new coronavirus.
Katri warned earlier this week that people must take action before the snowball gets bigger and bigger, eventually causing an "avalanche."
In order to curb the rebound of the epidemic, Belgian Prime Minister Sophie Vermes announced on the 23rd that the relevant rules for people to wear masks in public places will be stricter, and the plan to further lift restrictive measures in August will also be suspended.
