Xinhua News Agency, Hong Kong, July 25 - Edward Yau, Secretary for Commerce and Economic Development of the Hong Kong SAR Government, said on the 25th that all APEC member economies should act in unison to fight the epidemic and promote economic recovery, and should avoid unnecessary trade barriers in accordance with the rights and obligations stipulated by the World Trade Organization.
Yau made the remarks while participating in a video conference of trade ministers to combat the novel coronavirus outbreak held by the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) on the 25th.
In this meeting, the participating ministers exchanged views on APEC's response to the impact of the new coronavirus epidemic and the substantive solutions that can be taken to promote economic recovery in the region.
Yau said the public health and economic crisis triggered by the epidemic has had an unprecedented and far-reaching impact on society and the economy.
"We are in a dual battle. We must first defeat the epidemic before we can save the economy.
We must have a clear goal, the virus is our common enemy, cooperation can win, otherwise it will only fail. ”
Yau said that the series of trade restrictions triggered by the new crown pneumonia epidemic will not help control the epidemic.
Trade is a key remedy to the current problems and should not be seen as the problem.
He condemned all discriminatory and divisive policy measures and urged all economies to keep their borders open, maintain the smooth functioning of supply chains and avoid erecting trade barriers or adopting irrational trade policies at this critical time.
414,000 new coronavirus cases confirmed in Florida, making it the second worst-hit state in the US
China News Service, July 26: According to a comprehensive report, the website of Johns Hopkins University in the United States shows that as of 8:34 a.m. Beijing time on the 26th, Florida in the United States reported more than 414,000 new coronavirus confirmed cases, surpassing New York State's 411,000, becoming the second largest "epidemic area" in the United States after California.
The Florida Department of Health said on the 25th that Florida reported 124 deaths on the 24th.
This is the tenth time that Florida's daily death toll has exceeded 100 since the start of the pandemic.
It is reported that the total number of cases in Miami-Dade County, the most affected area in Florida, has exceeded 100,000.
Florida currently has 8,974 coronavirus hospitalizations, including 1,874 in Miami-Dade.
Since July 4, the number of coronavirus hospitalizations in the state has increased by 79%.
Since the first US state reopened on April 24, 91,000 lives have been claimed.
According to data provided by Johns Hopkins University, the total number of confirmed cases reported in the United States has reached 4.176 million, and at least 146,000 people have died.
Chengdu people gather to watch the US Consulate Police stop people from "looking too happy"
In response to the US closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, China announced the closure of the US Consulate General in Chengdu on Friday.
On Saturday, the US consulate's badge was removed, and on Sunday, a dark-glass car drove away from the consulate amid boos from passers-by.
On Sunday, many Chengdu people gathered in front of the U.S. Consulate to take pictures, and those who had not been there were also driven by curiosity about current affairs.
Agence France-Presse's Chengdu station reporter also went to the vicinity of the US Consulate in Chengdu to observe, and reported back that there were many curious people, and many parents took their children to take a walk to see the consulate, take pictures of the building, or take selfies.
The consulate was surrounded by guards, and the police "corrected" people's behavior from time to time, and they did not seem to allow any extraordinary behavior: a woman was stopped just as she was about to sing a red song, and a guard confiscated a banner.
But residents of a nearby residential building managed to pull up a giant Chinese flag on their balcony and shouted slogans in support of China.
Opened in 1985, the U.S. Consulate in Chengdu covers all U.S. consular-related matters in southwest China, especially in the Tibet Autonomous Region.
Agence France-Presse's Chengdu station reporter said that the Chinese government's response to the United States was relatively restrained: many Chinese people online asked the government to close the US consulate in Hong Kong, but the official only said that "the closure of the Chengdu US consulate is a necessary and legitimate response to the unreasonable behavior of the United States."
In addition to Chengdu, the United States currently has consulates in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan, and Hong Kong.
Large-scale financial media campaign "Go to the village live to see poverty alleviation" starts - Today's news - Hunan Daily News - Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily · New Hunan Client July 25th (Reporter of this newspaper) On July 25th, the large-scale financial media action "Walking Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation" sponsored by the Financial Program Center of the Central Radio and Television General Station departed from Xuzhou, Jiangsu, and two caravans carrying 5G new media mobile cloud broadcasting system were sent by the guests on the scene and slowly drove out of the scene.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that "2020 is a landmark year. We will build a moderately prosperous society in an all-round way and achieve the first centenary goal. 2020 is also the year of decisive victory in the fight against poverty."
The large-scale financial media campaign "Going to the Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation" is an important measure for the financial program center of the Central Radio and Television General Station to cooperate with this major theme and do a good job in promoting poverty alleviation.
The action will go into poverty-stricken villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government, dig up fresh stories of poverty alleviation, directly attack the dramatic changes in the appearance of villages, and show how villagers can break through the difficulties of survival and development and move towards the road to prosperity.
The operation will last for more than three months.
Starting from Xuzhou, the reporter divided into two routes and took the southwest route, passing through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; the other route took the northwest route, passing through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, covering more than 10,000 kilometers.
In the form of reporting, "Going to the village to see poverty alleviation" is boldly integrated.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcast through the CCTV Financial Channel of the Central Radio and Television General Station, the Voice of the Central Guangxi Economy, China Traffic Radio, and CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, the live TV broadcast will be mainly completed in the midday news program "Tianxia Caijing" of CCTV Finance Channel (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 12:00-13:00), and the gold news program "Economic Information Network" of CCTV Finance Channel will open a column on poverty alleviation (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 20:30-21:30).
At the same time, the caravan will conduct a one-hour live broadcast on the CCTV financial client for each village it visits. Viewers can watch the live broadcast and participate in the lottery by downloading the CCTV financial app.
In terms of technology application and studio design, "Walking Village Live to See Poverty Alleviation" bravely broke through and pioneered the "New Media Caravan in the Outfield."
The car is equipped with a 5G new media mobile cloud broadcasting system, using 5G + 4K / 8K + AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, large screen and small screen, and television broadcasting.
Equipped with a three-channel studio area, the studio area is converted from a container, with a length of 12 meters, a width of 2.55 meters, and a height of 3.98 meters. The box adopts a hydraulic automatic unfolding structure, which can be turned up to 120 degrees.
The studio area can also be automatically expanded and connected to an external expansion platform, with an area of more than 50 square meters, which can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
At present, the Dongchuan District of Kunming is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
"Now, as soon as I leave home, I go to the factory to earn money and take care of my family, thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the trade union," said Lu Ling, an employee of Kunming Esfu Electronic Technology Company.
Walking into the poverty alleviation workshop of electronic components processing in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a hot and busy picture came into view.
Lu Ling, who is in her 40s, is a single mother, raising her children alone and caring for her elderly parents.
In her most difficult time, the Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped to come up with ideas and find ways to "send charcoal in the snow."
Since 2018, Lu Ling has enjoyed housing, schooling, social security, employment and other assistance policies and assistance funds issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her children have successfully graduated and are employed, and she herself has a job and income after participating in skills training, and has been out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that the special skills training project of the Dongchuan District General Organization to help poverty alleviation is part of the skills training work of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions.
Combined with the characteristics of the difficult workers in the poverty alleviation and relocation resettlement sites in the area, the district has conducted in-depth investigations to understand the training needs and determine the types of training. In the near future, it plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders, pastry chefs, etc.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Yunnan Menglian County Branch of the Agricultural Bank, wrote a sincere letter of thanks to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In her letter, she sincerely thanked the union for giving her a scholarship from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the file of difficult workers. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the policy of building a file.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been lifted out of poverty through institutional guarantees and targeted assistance.
The successful rescue of Lu Ling's family and Li Yi is a microcosm of the Yunnan trade union's work to promote the rescue of workers in difficulty.
According to Kaiyuan Duan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Department of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial government has strengthened the dynamic management of the files of employees in difficulty, promoted the normalization of the filing work, and promptly incorporated the help system for employees in difficulty who meet the filing conditions; broadened the application channels for employees in difficulty, and used WeChat to open an online application service platform for employees in difficulty to file, so as to facilitate the timely and active declaration of employees in difficulty.
During the epidemic, it is difficult to go out to work. In order to help the workers with difficulties in the file to ease the pressure of life, Yunnan Province has arranged more than 13 million yuan to send warm funds. According to the national standard of 2,000 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in the file and 1,500 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in the file at the provincial level, more than 6,000 households at the national level and more than 1,000 households at the provincial level have implemented special warm condolence activities for workers with difficulties in the file.
At the same time, the provincial government has linked up with various Internet recruitment platforms such as the Human Resources and Social Security Department and Zhaopin Recruitment to push recruitment information to workers in difficulty and provide employment counseling, employment guidance and other services.
